        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/439/1",
        "text": [
          " سَمِعْتُهُ یَقُولُ مَنِ اشْتَکَی لَیْلَهً فَقَبِلَهَا بِقَبُولِهَا وَ أَدَّی إِلَی اللَّهِ شُکْرَهَا کَانَتْ لَهُ کَفَّارَهُ سِتِّینَ سَنَهً قَالَ قُلْتُ وَ مَا مَعْنَی قَبِلَهَا بِقَبُولِهَا قَالَ صَبَرَ عَلَی مَا کَانَ فِیهَا."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1.  It is narrated that Imam Ja’far Sadiq (a.s.) said, “One who thanks Allah after bearing illness for a night, is compensated for his sins of sixty years.” The narrator asked the meaning of bearing. Imam  (a.s.) replied, “Remaining  patient during illness.”"
          ]
        }
      }
